TEXT(beginproblem());
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$b = random(2,6,1);
$a = $b + 1;

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));

Evaluate the integral by interpreting it in terms of areas:
$BR
$PAR
\( \displaystyle{ \int_{-$a}^{$a}  \left($b - |x| \right)\, dx} = \)
$PAR
   \{ans_rule(25) \}
$BR
$BR

EOT

$ans = $b**2 -1;

ANS(num_cmp($ans));

